Write a Java program to compute the area of a polygon.
Area of a polygon = (n*s^2)/(4*tan(Ï€/n))
where n is n-sided polygon and s is the length of a side.
Input Format
Input the number of sides on the polygon: 7
Input the length of one of the sides: 6
Output Format
The output prints represent the area of a polygon
Sample Input
10
Sample Output
5
The area is: 192.35522107345335
Sample Input
4
Sample Output
4
The area is: 16.000000000000004



package com.example.workout;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class area_polygen {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		double n=sc.nextDouble();
		double s=sc.nextDouble();
		double area=(n*(s*s))/(4*Math.tan(Math.PI/n));
		System.out.println("The area of polygen:"+area);
		sc.close();

	}

}
